Hotel Reservation Analysis with SQL
Overview:
The hotel industry relies on data to make informed decisions and provide a better guest experience. In
this internship,you will work with a hotel reservation dataset to gain insights into guest preferences,
booking trends, and other key factors that impact the hotel's operations. You will use SQL to query and
analyze the data, as well as answer specific questions about the dataset.

Skills Demonstrated
Basic SQL Querying
Grouping Data
Filtering Data
Aggregation Function
Sorting Results
Date Functions
Data Types and Conversion

Tool Used
This project was completed using MySQL, leveraging its robust database management capabilities to store, manage, and analyze data, and drive project outcome.

Insight from the Dataset
There are 700 reservations made, 493 reservations was confirmed while 207 was canceled. 
The most commonly booked room type = Room_Type_1 with 534 rooms booked.
The most commonly used market segment type for reservation = Online
